ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: If set to true, the cell will be disabled if the time and phase synchronization accuracy of the eNodeB is not fulfilled.
The value component of the RDN.
Label for free use.
Refers to the SCTP instance that is used to configure the SCTP host for S1 and X2 connections.

Controls if the Tracking Area Identity (TAI) is used to get IP addresses of MME nodes from the Domain Name System (DNS).
The RBS uses TAI to automatically obtain all MME IP addresses from the DNS when dnsLookupOnTai is switched on, or at RBS start or restart.
The MME IP address list is refreshed periodically and MME connections released and setup according to the new list. The MME IP address list can also be refreshed from OSS-RC.
The interval to perform DNS Lookup to get potential new IP addresses of MME nodes. DNS lookup is performed for the TAI domain name. If the value is set to zero, then no periodic DNS Lookup is done.
Static mapping of DiffServ label for control messages, Performance Management (PM), and Non-Access Stratum (NAS).
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Will only be used then dscpUsage is active.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The ENodeB ID that forms part of the Cell Global Identity, and is also used to identify the node over the S1 interface.

The ENodeB Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) ID that forms part of the ENodeB Global ID used to identify the node over the S1 interface. Note: The value (MCC=001, MNC=01) indicates that the PLMN is not initiated. The value can not be used as a valid PLMN Identity.
A list of blacklisted RBS IDs. X2 may not be set up to any neighbor RBS in the blacklist.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: If an eNB is added to the list, any termPointToEnb for this external eNB is removed.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: See attribute x2RetryTimerStart.

After failed X2 setup and after X2 link break the x2RetryTimer is used to control the time till next retry. x2RetryTimer is used for DNS, SCTP, X2AP retries and x2IpAddrViaS1.
After first failed setup or missing IP address from DNS, x2RetryTimer = max(x2RetryTimerStart,W), where W is the timeToWait received in x2SetupFail. If W is not received, W=0.
After link break, x2RetryTimer = random(0,x2RetryTimerStart). If the first setup after link break fails, the timer values according to the above and below paragraphs shall apply as for failed inital setup.
After 2nd and following fails, if the X2 connection is not being setup by ANR in the S-RBS, x2RetryTimer = max(x2RetryTimerStart,W).
After 2nd and following fails, if the X2 connection is being setup by ANR in the S-RBS, x2RetryTimer = max(min[2^(n-2)*x2RetryTimerStart, x2retryTimerMaxAuto], W), where n is failure number.
Each W is only used in the first retry after it is received.
The list of whitelisted RBS IDs. Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) is not allowed to disconnect X2 for any neighbor RBS in the whitelist.
Defines the frequency to perform re-establishment of SCTP and S1-AP connection, when the connection to a MME is lost.
Specifies if the advanced UL scheduler is enabled
Refers to the IpAccessHostEt instance to use for configuring the IP access host for S1 and X2 user plane connections. This attribute must contain a valid MO reference if the IPsec function is used.
Indicates if the function X2 IP addresses over S1 is active in the RBS.

The mode used by the RBS for the non-access stratum node selection.
Regardless of the mode used, the function attempts to:
- Reconnect every UE to its registered MME in any of the tracking areas of the cell.
- Distribute the UEs that are not reconnected among MMEs that serve the Public Land Mobile Network selected by each UE.
Indicates if the feature RRC Connection Reestablishment is ACTIVATED or DEACTIVATED.

This parameter indicates if two way relations shall be setup during X2 setup and eNB configuration. The RBS creates a two-way relation for each entry in the received neighbour information that contains a relation to a source cell. Neighbour information is sent in X2 setup and eNB configuration. Neighbour information is eUtranCellRelations per source cell from the sending node.

This counter counts the number of received S1AP Paging messages in the RBS. Both non prioritized and prioritized S1AP Paging messages are included.

The number of S1AP Paging messages that are discarded (and not routed to any cell) due to that the maximum number of incoming S1AP Paging messages during a certain time interval is reached. This counter is a subset of pmPagS1Received. Both non prioritized and prioritized S1AP Paging messages are included.

S1 Handover data forwarding can be of two types, direct and indirect. Direct forwarding requires direct connectivity between source and target eNodeB. This parameter is used to indicate if such direct connectivity exist.

Random number update interval This attribute specifies the time interval in minutes between random number generation. When this interval expires, the eNodeB generates a new random number between MinRandc and MaxRandc.

This counter specifies the current footprint in the eNB from the configured MO instances for all different Cell Relations and External Cells in relation to the MO system limit. The higher the value, the more internal memory is consumed in the eNB for MO instances for the different types of Cell Relations and External Cells. The value is the highest sampled value during a ROP period. When the value reaches 100, further creation attempts for MO instances are rejected.

Supervision timer of the outgoing LTE to CDMA 1xRtt handover execution procedure.
Current number of licensed 5+5 MHz Sector Carrier capacity units that are allocated to cells.

In order to send a UE to WiFi, a throughput comparison is made between WiFi and LTE. For comparisons made in eNodeB, a UE is admitted to WiFi if, WiFi throughput > biasThpWifiMobility * LTE throughput.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Number of RIM reports received that contain an error message.
Peak number of active RIM associations, that is, the rimAssociationStatus parameter value is RIM_ACTIVE.

The timeout time for receiving HANDOVER CANCEL ACKNOWLEDGE after RBS sent HO CANCEL message to MME. Value specifies supervision time of outgoing S1 HO Cancellation according to procedure described in 3GPP TS 36.413 section 8.4.5.

Controls DNS selection for S1 and X2 lookups. If not set, DNS server on OAM network is used.
For DU Radio Node it can be set to reference a DnsResolver, and DNS queries are resolved using referenced DnsResolver (typically using DNS server on transport network).
For Baseband Radio Node it can be set to reference a DnsClient, and DNS queries are resolved using referenced DnsClient (typically using DNS server on transport network).
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:preCondition: To enable this attribute DNS servers must support EDNS0.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:lifeCycleDesc: Since L16A. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Controls if the release of inactive UEs at handover shall be enabled.
Inactivity time value to be used to decide release of inactive UEs at handover.
Minimum MP load level at which inactive UEs are released at handover.
Used for PDSCH and PHICH sector selection in combined Cell. For each Ue, all sectors received power are compared against the primary sector. Sectors that are below the threshold will be selected.

Used for PUSCH sector selection in combined Cell. For each Ue, all sectors received power are compared against the primary sector. Only the primary and the best sector that is below the threshold will be selected.

The maximum allowed time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB. It is the deviation that is allowed for SIB16 Time Information Broadcast feature to function. When the limit is exceeded, the feature is deactivated.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Traffic can be affected if this attribute is changed. It can cause malfunction of the SIB16 Time Information Broadcast due to the time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The maximum allowed time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB. It is the deviation that is allowed for Multimedia Broadcast Multicast Service (MBMS) to function. When the limit is exceeded, the service is deactivated.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Traffic can be affected if this attribute is changed. It can cause malfunction of the Multimedia Broadcast Multicast Service (MBMS) due to the time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The maximum allowed time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB. It is the deviation that is allowed for Observed Time Difference of Arrival (OTDOA) Support to function. When the limit is exceeded, the service is deactivated.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Traffic can be affected if this attribute is changed. It can cause malfunction of the Observed Time Difference of Arrival (OTDOA) Support feature due to the time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The maximum allowed time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB. It is the deviation that is allowed for features related to CDMA2000 fallback and handover to function. When the limit is exceeded, some of the functionality is deactivated.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Traffic can be affected if this attribute is changed. It can cause malfunction of the features related to CDMA2000 due to the time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The maximum allowed time and phase deviation for time and phase synchronization of the eNodeB for TDD cells. When the limit is exceeded, the TDD cells get disabled.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Set to false when the SIB16 Time Information Broadcast feature is degraded due to time and phase synchronization accuracy requirements not fulfilled, otherwise it is set to true.
Set to false when the Multimedia Broadcast Multicast Service (MBMS) feature is degraded due to time and phase synchronization accuracy requirements not fulfilled, otherwise it is set to true.
Set to false when the Observed Time Difference of Arrival (OTDOA) feature is degraded due to time and phase synchronization accuracy requirements not fulfilled, otherwise it is set to true.
Set to false when the features related to CDMA2000 are degraded due to time and phase synchronization accuracy requirements not fulfilled, otherwise it is set to true.
If set to true, any time and phase synchronization accuracy-dependent feature is deactivated or degraded if its time and phase synchronization accuracy is not fulfilled.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Current number of licensed 5+5 MHz Sector Carrier capacity units that are allocated to FDD cells. If the node has no FDD cells unlocked then counter reports 0 value.
Current number of licensed 5+5 MHz Sector Carrier capacity units that are allocated to TDD cells. If the node has no TDD cells unlocked then counter reports 0 value.
The percentile to use for the counter pmLicConnectedUsersActual.
The percentile to use for the counter BbProcessingResource::pmLicDlCapActual.
The percentile to use for the counter BbProcessingResource::pmLicUlCapActual.
The percentile to use for the counter BbProcessingResource::pmLicDlPrbCapActual.
The percentile to use for the counter BbProcessingResource::pmLicUlPrbCapActual.

The X percentile of the utilization for connected users during a measurement period. The value for X is set in the attribute licConnectedUsersPercentileConf.
Source Data: licConnectedUsersPercentileConf and pmLicConnectedUsersDistr
Number of times pmLicConnectedUsersLevSum has been incremented. Associated ACC pmCounter pmLicConnectedUsersLevSum.
Sum of all sample values recorded for "Connected Users".

The licensed value for connected users. The value reflects the capacity value in the license key file, that is the value of the attribute licensedCapacity in the CapacityConnectedUsers instance of the MO class CapacityFeatureLicense. If the value is -100, it means the Connected Users feature uses the Not Contractually Limited model.
Source attribute: CapacityFeatureLicense::licensedCapacity in CapacityConnectedUsers instance of CapacityFeatureLicense.
Peak number of Connected Users.
Accumulated time during the ROP when the number of connected users is equal to or greater than the licensed value.

The licensed capacity limit for downlink baseband capacity. The value reflects the capacity value in the license key file, that is the value of the attribute licensedCapacity in the DlBasebandCapacity instance of the MO class CapacityFeatureLicense.
Source attribute: CapacityFeatureLicense::licensedCapacity in DlBasebandCapacity instance of CapacityFeatureLicense.

The licensed capacity limit for uplink baseband capacity. The value reflects the capacity value in the license key file, that is the value of the attribute licensedCapacity in the UlBasebandCapacity instance of the MO class CapacityFeatureLicense.
Source attribute: CapacityFeatureLicense::licensedCapacity in UlBasebandCapacity instance of CapacityFeatureLicense.

The licensed capacity limit for DL PRB capacity. The value reflects the capacity value in the license key file, that is the value of the attribute licensedCapacity in the DlPrbCapacity instance of the MO class CapacityFeatureLicense.. If the value is -100, it means DL PRB capacity uses the Not Contractually Limited model.
Source attribute: CapacityFeatureLicense::licensedCapacity in DlPrbCapacity instance of CapacityFeatureLicense.

The licensed capacity limit for UL PRB capacity. The value reflects the capacity value in the license key file, that is the value of the attribute licensedCapacity in the UlPrbCapacity instance of the MO class CapacityFeatureLicense.. If the value is -100, it means UL PRB capacity uses the Not Contractually Limited model.
Source attribute: CapacityFeatureLicense::licensedCapacity in UlPrbCapacity instance of CapacityFeatureLicense.
Enables or disables the RRC Connection Reestablishment in source cell when there is no target neighbor cell information.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: This attribute is only effective when feature Multi-Target RRC Connection Reestablishment is activated.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Used to turn on and off the function for checking existence of emergency calls.
Length of waiting time before soft-lock of cell starts to release all ongoing calls with Release with Redirect (RwR), when eNodeB internally triggers soft-lock of cell.
Length of waiting time before soft-lock of cell starts to release all ongoing calls with Release with Redirect (RwR), when operator triggers soft-lock of cell.
A policy parameter that sets the start value of the attribute mfbiSupport when an ExternalENodeBFunction is automatically created by the eNodeB.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Shows if Adaptive RLC Retransmission in DL is active or not.

The targeted maximum allowed time between scheduling occasions of an UL bearer. A bearer that is not scheduled within the specified time is given higher priority. Value 0 means that the higher priority is never applied. It is recommended to set the value =< than the PDB. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect performance of all data bearers. A value that is set too low can affect other services with higher priority. A value that is set too high can cause Dynamic UE Admission Control to fail in keeping the cell stable at overload.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only used for Resource Fair Scheduling algorithm. Only relevant if the license for Dynamic UE Admission Control is present and the feature is active.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Supervision timer of the outgoing S1/X2/intra-eNodeB handover execution procedure according to 3GPP TS 36.413 and TS 36.423. If the feature Multi-Target RRC Connection Re-establishment is active this timer also supervises the Context Fetch procedure.

ns2:primaryTypeAction.ns1:desc:
This action shall make it possible to order the RBS to make a new DNS lookup to get possible new MME Pool addresses. The orderCode has two different options:
- Retain: This option will retain all connections that were included in DNS response and the connections that were not included in the response will be removed. For the IP addresses that were unknown for the RBS, the RBS will establish connections to those MMEs.
- Renew All existing: The RBS performs a DNS lookup. Release all S1 connections to the MMEs and connect to the MMEs that are included in the DNS response.
This action should be used only when dnsLookupOnTai has the value ON. The action is rejected if dnsLookupState has the value OFF.
Returns a snapshot of the traffic status of the node divided per cell, in the form; number of attached UEs and set up radio bearers.

ns2:parameter.ns1:desc: Specifies the format of the returned information. It can be either of: - Unformatted text, suitable for on-screen reading. - Formatted text, suitable for automated interpretation, currently JSON (JavaScript Object Notation).
